mcp-ollama-python for Debian
============================

This is a Debian/Ubuntu package for mcp-ollama-python, a Model Context
Protocol (MCP) server that exposes local Ollama models as tools for AI
assistants.

PREREQUISITES
=============

Before using mcp-ollama-python, ensure you have:

1. Ollama installed and running (https://ollama.ai)
   Start with: ollama serve

2. At least one model installed in Ollama
   Download with: ollama pull <model-name>
   Example: ollama pull mistral

INSTALLATION
============

After package installation, the following commands are available:

  mcp-ollama-python      # Main MCP server
  mcp-interactive        # Interactive testing interface
  mcp-server-control     # Server control utility

USAGE WITH AI ASSISTANTS
=========================

1. Claude Desktop Configuration
   Edit ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json:

   {
     "mcpServers": {
       "ollama": {
         "command": "mcp-ollama-python",
         "env": {"OLLAMA_HOST": "http://localhost:11434"}
       }
     }
   }

2. VS Code / Windsurf Configuration
   Edit your MCP configuration file:

   {
     "mcpServers": {
       "ollama": {
         "command": "mcp-ollama-python",
         "env": {"OLLAMA_HOST": "http://localhost:11434"}
       }
     }
   }

INTERACTIVE TESTING
===================

Test the server and tools interactively:

  mcp-interactive

This opens an interactive console to test all available Ollama tools.

SERVER CONTROL
==============

Manage the server process:

  mcp-server-control start      # Start the server
  mcp-server-control stop       # Stop the server
  mcp-server-control status     # Check server status
  mcp-server-control logs       # View server logs

CONFIGURATION
=============

Configure behavior via environment variables:

  OLLAMA_HOST
    Ollama server URL (default: http://localhost:11434)
    Example: OLLAMA_HOST=http://192.168.1.100:11434

  OLLAMA_TIMEOUT
    Request timeout in seconds (default: 30)
    Example: OLLAMA_TIMEOUT=60

  LOG_LEVEL
    Logging level: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR (default: INFO)
    Example: LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG

Export variables in your shell profile or systemd service to make them
permanent:

  export OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
  export LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG

SYSTEMD SERVICE (Optional)
==========================

Create /etc/systemd/user/mcp-ollama.service:

  [Unit]
  Description=Ollama MCP Server
  After=network.target
  
  [Service]
  Type=simple
  ExecStart=/usr/bin/mcp-ollama-python
  Restart=on-failure
  RestartSec=10
  Environment="OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434"
  
  [Install]
  WantedBy=default.target

Then enable with:
  systemctl --user enable mcp-ollama
  systemctl --user start mcp-ollama

LOG FILES
=========

Log output is sent to stderr by default. For persistent logging with
systemd, view with:

  journalctl --user -u mcp-ollama -f

TROUBLESHOOTING
===============

Q: "Connection refused" errors
A: Ensure Ollama is running with `ollama serve`

Q: "Model not found" errors
A: Pull a model first with `ollama pull <model-name>`

Q: Server crashes on startup
A: Check with `LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG` to see detailed errors

Q: Slow responses
A: Check OLLAMA_TIMEOUT setting; increase if needed

